{"id":"6779","name":"PasteBin Pasting","tagline":"Send content to PasteBin","icon":"ios14 c946986751 g59708","latest":"29616","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><img alt=\"PasteBin Pasting\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/qKBuf9u.png\"></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Welcome to PasteBin Pasting!</p>\n<p>This shortcut will guide you through setup while running for the first time. </p>\n<p>It will prompt you for your API key, which gets stored in your iCloud Drive/Shortcuts folder for security. </p>\n<p>The running process of the shortcut is:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>On first run</strong>: Prompt user for PasteBin API key (found at <a href=\"https://pastebin.com/doc_api#1\">PasteBin</a>)<ul>\n<li>This is saved to iCloud Drive in the PasteBin Pasting settings.json file</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Check for shortcut input from share sheet<ul>\n<li>If share sheet has no value, then prompt user for content to paste and suggest clipboard</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Prompt user for name of the paste</li>\n<li>Prompt user for expiration duration<ul>\n<li>Never</li>\n<li>10 min</li>\n<li>1 hour</li>\n<li>1 day</li>\n<li>1 week</li>\n<li>2 weeks</li>\n<li>1 month</li>\n<li>6 months</li>\n<li>1 year</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Prompt user for privacy type<ul>\n<li>Public</li>\n<li>Unlisted</li>\n<li>Private (requires user login)\n<strong>Note</strong> If privacy type is set to Private, then the user will be promoted for login info. This information is NOT stored by the shortcut. It is only used to generate the api_user_key per the PasteBin documentation (only on the first time of using private or log to account feature)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>If privacy type is NOT set to Private, then the user is asked \"Do you want to log this to your account?\"<ul>\n<li>Answering yes will prompt the user for the login info mentioned above. </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Resulting PasteBin link is then copied to the clipboard and the user is shown a quicklook page with a tappable link to the PasteBin page</li>\n</ul>\n<h5>Runtime Screenshots</h5>\n<h6>API Key and Input</h6>\n<p><img alt=\"API Key and Input\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/WF1Ii70.jpg\"></p>\n<h6>Paste Name and Expiration</h6>\n<p><img alt=\"Name and Exp\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/PgNEUVn.jpg\"></p>\n<h6>Privacy and Save to Account</h6>\n<p><img alt=\"Priv and Account\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/nZKZ1DL.jpg\"></p>\n<h6>Login Info (Not Stored)</h6>\n<p><img alt=\"Login\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/3p0sF92.jpg\"></p>\n<h6>Final output preview</h6>\n<p><img alt=\"Output\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/PsMH7PB.png\"></p>\n<p>Thanks to pfg for Embed-a-Update used in this shortcut and to ROP for MediaKit used to make the badge on this page</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.1 - Sept. 9, 2021, 8:46 a.m.</strong></p><p>Version 1.1 Release Notes<br>- Moved the ToPaste variable and it's if statement to the top of the shortcut to address an issue where the shortcut settings file was also being included in the paste (this was due to a change in the way the iOS 14 Add To Variable action worked.<br><br>- Total Actions: #76<br>- Created on iOS 14.7.1<br>- Released at Sep 9, 2021</p>"}